Nine people have been injured after a taxi lost control and rolled coming to rest on its roof in Loft Road in Wyebank Pinetown.The accident happened on Tuesday afternoon just after 15:45.Rescue Care&#8217;s Garrith Jamieson said paramedics arrived on the scene to find that a single taxi had somehow lost control and rolled coming to rest on its roof. A total of nine patients were stabilised on the scene with injuries ranging from minor to moderate injuries. Multiple ambulances were used to transport the injured to various Durban Hospitals for the further care that they required.At this stage the exact cause of the collision is unknown however SAPS were on scene and will be investigating further.!